R1 6lr2621
By: Delegates Nawrocki, Allen, Arikan, Behler, Boyce, Guyton, Jacobs, T. Morgan,
and Szeliga Szeliga, Baker, Grammer, Healey, Lewis, and Stein
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 9, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Highway Administration Highways – Highway Work Permits – Notice
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the State Highway Administration an applicant for a certain
4 work permit on a State highway to immediately provide certain notice including
5 certain information to certain members of the General Assembly of an application
6 for a work permit on a State highway; and generally relating to notice of work
7 permits for State highways.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
9 Article – Transportation
10 Section 8–646(a) and (b)(1) and (2)
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 BY adding to
14 Article – Transportation
15 Section 8–646(e)
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2020 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
20 Article – Transportation
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb1508*

2 HOUSE BILL 1508
1 8–646.
2 (a) Except as permitted by this section or in accordance with a permit obtained
3 from the Administration, a person may not:
4 (1) Make an opening in any State highway;
5 (2) Place any structure on any State highway;
6 (3) Change or renew any structure placed on any State highway;
7 (4) Dig up any State highway for any purpose, including the placement of
8 pipes, sewers, poles, wires, or rails;
9 (5) Plant or remove any tree on any State highway; or
10 (6) Place any obstruction or improvement on any State highway.
11 (b) (1) The Administration may issue a permit for work otherwise prohibited
12 by subsection (a) of this section.
13 (2) Work done under the permit shall be performed to the satisfaction of
14 the Administration and under its supervision.
15 (E) (1) ON RECEIPT OF WITHIN 10 DAYS AFTER AN APPLICANT SUBMITS
16 AN APPLICATION FOR A PERMIT UNDER THIS SECTION FOR A TYPE 2 OR TYPE 3
17 PROJECT, AS DESIGNATED BY THE ADMINISTRATION, THE ADMINISTRATION, IN
18 ACCORDANCE WITH § 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, THE
19 APPLICANT SHALL IMMEDIATELY PROVIDE NOTICE OF THE APPLICATION TO EACH
20 MEMBER OF THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY WHO REPRESENTS THE STATE LEGISLATIVE
21 DISTRICT IN WHICH THE PROPOSED WORK IS TO BE PERFORMED.
22 (2) THE NOTICE REQUIRED UNDER THIS SUBSECTION SHALL
23 INCLUDE:
24 (I) THE NAME OF THE APPLICANT;
25 (II) THE LOCATION OF THE PROPOSED WORK;
26 (III) THE EXPECTED STARTING DATE FOR THE PROPOSED WORK;
27 AND
28 (IV) A BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF THE NATURE OF THE PROPOSED
29 WORK.

HOUSE BILL 1508 3
1 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
2 1, 2026.
